---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import ArrayVisualizer from '../../components/visualizers/ArrayVisualizer';
---

<MainLayout title="Arrays">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Arrays</h1>
    
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Introduction to Arrays</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
        An array is a fundamental data structure that stores elements in contiguous memory locations.
        Understanding arrays is crucial as they form the basis for many other data structures and algorithms.
      </p>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Key Concepts</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
          <li>Contiguous memory allocation</li>
          <li>Zero-based indexing</li>
          <li>Fixed size (in most implementations)</li>
          <li>Direct access to elements</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Learning Path</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <a href="/arrays/basics" class="block p-4 bg-indigo-50 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-100 transition-colors">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-800 mb-2">1. Basic Operations</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Learn fundamental array operations: access, insert, delete, and traverse</p>
          </a>
          
          <a href="/arrays/memory" class="block p-4 bg-indigo-50 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-100 transition-colors">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-800 mb-2">2. Memory Management</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Understand how arrays are stored in memory and their implications</p>
          </a>
          
          <a href="/arrays/patterns" class="block p-4 bg-indigo-50 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-100 transition-colors">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-800 mb-2">3. Common Patterns</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Master common array patterns and problem-solving strategies</p>
          </a>
          
          <a href="/arrays/techniques" class="block p-4 bg-indigo-50 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-100 transition-colors">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-indigo-800 mb-2">4. Advanced Techniques</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Learn advanced techniques like Two Pointers, Sliding Window, and more</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Interactive Visualization</h3>
        <ArrayVisualizer client:load />
      </div>

      <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-yellow-800 mb-2">Pro Tip</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Master the basics before moving on to advanced techniques. A solid understanding of array fundamentals
          will make learning complex algorithms much easier.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>